matched_jobs.description:
Your skills:

- You can drive the project from start to finish, minimizing the time to deliver value to customers;
- You understand how important role in product delivery plays communication;
-  You’re a well-organized person, willing to push other people to be well-organized too;
- You’re experienced with finding the best trade-offs, supported by knowledge gathered from stakeholders;
- You’re experienced with agile methods, limiting dependencies and waterfall whenever possible;
- You can help all employees understand the why, how and what regarding the project you’re delivering;
- You empower teams by leading by example;
- You’re asking WHY first;
- You’re fluent in written/spoken English.

- 3 years production DBA experience;
- A solid understanding of database backup and restore methods;
- Understanding of the difference between full, differential, log and tail of log backups;
- Understanding of backup chains and their effect on log shipping;
- Experience of working with sensitive information;
- Understanding of the importance of and impact of consistency checks on live databases;
- Experience of dealing with corruption in a production environment;
- A solid understanding of the security hierarchy (AD, SQL logins, database users) in SQL Server;
- Experience with deploying and managing encryption across production and test environments;
- Experience with DR techniques, such as log shipping and Always On Availability Groups;
- Experience with installing and configuring new SQL Server instances;
- Good understanding of database maintenance;
- Strong knowledge of T-SQL (with experience of debugging T-SQL);
- Performance tuning.

- At least 3 years of experience in testing;
- Strong QA skills including planning, testing and defect reporting;
- Experience in creating test plans, test strategies, test cases and test automation;
- Experience in designing and developing an automated test environment for large complex systems;
- Knowledge on modern web services;
- Understanding of continuous integrations systems;
- Understanding of version control systems, such as GitHub;
- Good knowledge of Python language;
- Object-oriented design and programming skills;
- Analytical mind and problem-solving aptitude;
- Strong verbal and written communication skills.

