- you’re focused on solving problems, passionate about delivering value for customers and have a strong business sense;
- you’re leading the team and product process with ease: from ideation to development and maintenance;
- you’re experienced in agile development: you gather feedback and insight from customers, frame a problem or need, propose a solution for it and deliver it with a team in iterations;
- you can transfer complex topics and projects into easy-to-understand messages and you have a strong communication skill;
- tasks like writing user stories, talking with customers, idea research, task prioritization, OKRs, daily standups, feature mockups are a piece of cake for you;
- you have a good understanding of the SaaS business model as well as the related concepts like churn, retention and so on;
- you’re not scared of taking risks and ditching a part of unsuccessful test or product;
- you know how to properly conduct an A/B test;
- you can articulate a compelling vision for your team and can motivate them to build a world-leading product and you know how to lead your team by example and empower them.

- you’re passionate about user-centered design, customers and creating an online product that’s delivering a purpose and value for them;
- you’re customers’ advocate and you act as a liaison between users and product teams;
- you’re experienced with both qualitative and quantitative research methods and synthesizing gathered data into solutions;
- you can drive a research process by yourself, from identifying an exploration area, through planning research and getting a product team involved in it, to drawing conclusions and suggesting prioritised solutions;
- you’ve conducted many remote research sessions and usability tests with customers in English – both before and after the solution was released;
- you’re analytical thinker and can synthesize and communicate ideas;
- you’re very communicative, you can explain user behaviour, expectations and ideas to the team and you can conduct team discussions;
- you’re self-organized, disciplined and experienced with working as a user research team of one;
- you’re fluent in written/spoken English.

